	<text id="ruskin_to_mother_august_11_1867">
	
	    <header>
	        <inventNo>1996L00329</inventNo>
	    </header>
	
	    <body>
	        <div type="text">
	            <pb n="1"/>
	            <ab id="ab1">
	                <p id="p1">
	                    <s id="s1">Your <hi rend="underline">real</hi> letter will come as usual tomorrow morning.</s>
	                    <s id="s2">But turn leaf of this.</s>
	                </p>
	            </ab>
	            <opener>
	                <placeName><!-- match letter exactly, delete if unnecessary -->
	                    <rs key="Q391805" type="place">Ambleside</rs><!-- not sure that this is in the letter? -->
	                </placeName>
	                <date when="1867-08-11"><!-- match letter exactly, delete if unnecessary -->
	                    <rs type="date">Sunday Evening</rs>
	                </date>
	                <salute>My dearest <rs key="47637407" type="person">Mother</rs>,</salute><!-- match letter exactly, delete if
	                unnecessary -->
	            </opener>
	
	            <p id="p2">
	                <s id="s3">I read your little enquiry and sentence about <rs key="8821113" type="person">Downes</rs>, to <rs key="8821113" type="person">Downes</rs> himself - much to his contentment</s>
	                <s id="s4">All the fine weather - hills - and <rs key="Q80005" type="flora">ferns</rs>, will not keep him any
	                    longer from his duties and you.</s>
	                <s id="s3">He has added much to my enjoyment of my excursions and I am sure, will be glad to tell
	                    you about them; he has
	                    <del rend="strikethrough">taken</del><add hand="#JR" place="above">made</add> the best out of
	                    his advantages.</s>
	            </p>
	
	            <p id="p3">
	                <s id="s4">I feel <del rend="strikethrough">to</del> just as if I was introducing a new Gardener to
	                    you, and giving him a character-</s>
	                <s id="s5">I should be puzzled to "give him" a better than his own.</s>
	            </p>
	
	            <closer>
	                <salute>Ever my dearest <rs key="47637407" type="person">mother</rs>, your <expan>affect<ex
							cert="high"> ionat</ex>e</expan> son.</salute><!-- optional - delete if unnecessary -->
	                <signed><!-- optional - delete if unnecessary -->
	                    <rs key="73859585" type="person">J Ruskin.</rs>
	                </signed>
	             </closer>
	            <pb n="2"/>
	            <ab id="ab2"> <!-- could be a postscript? -->
	                <p id="p4">
	                    <s id="s6">Monday morning.</s>
	                    <s id="s7">Exquisite weather.</s>
	                    <s id="s8">1/2 past 7. <hi rend="underline">here</hi></s>
	                </p>
	
	                <p id="p5">
	                    <s id="s9">10 minutes to eight by <hi rend="underline">you</hi>, as I know by my Father's watch which I always wear, now; - <hi rend="underline">what
	                    </hi> a watch it is! for rightness I gave it a kiss, with my golden
	                        letter this morning.</s>
	                </p>
	
	                <p id="p6">
	                    <s id="s11">Look here - while <rs key="76205504" type="person">Joanna</rs> stays at home with us, might it not
	                        be better that I should come home for a little while, take you to <rs key="Q83434" type="place">Norwood</rs>, while I can still enjoy the country drives therefrom, and get the house cleaned! - I
	                        will write more of this tomorrow, it would I think be best to.</s>
	                </p>
	            </ab>
	            <postscript>
	
	            </postscript>
	
